Sentencas: The percolated or active triple phase boundary (TPB) length per unit volume of Ni-YSZ anode hollow fibers (HFs) containing 60 wt.% initial NiO and a spatially varying microstructure were measured using a focused ion beam (FIB)-SEM technique.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: The measured values of contiguous TPB density were interfaced with a 2-D distributed finite element model of a hollow fiber solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: The model was applied to simultaneously solve the ionic and electronic charge balances in the electrodes, which were modelled as overlying continuum materials with effective electronic and ionic conductivities.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: The model was used to predict the effects of anode microstructure on the distribution of current density, and anode activation polarization.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: Active TPB lengths of 2.63-8.63 mu m(-2) were measured for the anode depending on location in the fiber wall and local microstructure.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: The effective anode ionic conductivity was predicted to be crucial to spreading the reaction zone from the anode/electrolyte interface toward the anode current collector.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs

Sentencas: For equal TPB distributions, faster electrochemical kinetics was predicted to constrain anode reaction current generation to within a few micrometers of the anode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Modelling the effects of measured anode triple-phase boundary densities on the performance of micro-tubular hollow fiber SOFCs
